  "local_port": 57210,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Which are the 4 stroke bikes in India?",
  "response": "In India, the popularity of motorcycles has seen a significant rise, with a diverse range of options catering to various riding preferences and budgets. When it comes to 4-stroke bikes, the market offers a plethora of choices, each with its unique features and specifications. Here, we'll explore some of the prominent 4-stroke motorcycles available in India, delving into their engine capacities, performance metrics, and distinctive characteristics.\n\n### 1. **Bajaj Pulsar Series**\n\n**a. Bajaj Pulsar 150**\n\n- **Engine:** 149.5 cc, 4-stroke, air-cooled\n- **Power:** 14 PS @ 8000 rpm\n- **Torque:** 13.25 Nm @ 6000 rpm\n- **Features:** Twin Spark DTS-i technology, electric start, tubeless tyres\n- **Target Audience:** Young riders looking for a powerful yet affordable sports bike\n\n**b. Bajaj Pulsar NS200**\n\n- **Engine:** 199.5 cc, 4-stroke, oil-cooled\n- **Power:** 24.5 PS @ 9750 rpm\n- **Torque:** 18.74 Nm @ 8000 rpm\n- **Features:** Stylized graphics, perimeter analog-digital console, front and rear disc brakes\n- **Target Audience:** Serious enthusiasts seeking a high-performance street bike\n\n### 2. **Hero Splendor Plus**\n\n- **Engine:** 97.2 cc, 4-stroke, air-cooled\n- **Power:** 8.02 PS @ 8000 rpm\n- **Torque:** 8.05 Nm @ 5000 rpm\n- **Features:** i3S (Idle StartStop System), traditional design, fuel efficiency\n- **Target Audience:** Commuters prioritizing fuel economy and reliability\n\n### 3. **TVS Apache RTR 160 4V**\n\n- **Engine:** 159.7 cc, 4-stroke, oil-cooled\n- **Power:** 16.02 PS @ 8500 rpm\n- **Torque:** 14.73 Nm @ 7000 rpm\n- **Features:** Race tuned suspension, Race dynamic tuning, slipper clutch, triple racing mode\n- **Target Audience:** Urban riders desiring a blend of performance and features\n\n### 4. **Royal Enfield Classic 350**\n\n- **Engine:** 346 cc, 4-stroke, air-cooled\n- **Power:** 19.1 PS @ 5250 rpm\n- **Torque:** 28 Nm @ 4000 rpm\n- **Features:** Classic styling, long stroke engine, comfortable seat\n- **Target Audience:** Riders appreciative of vintage aesthetics and relaxed cruising\n\n### Comparing 4-Stroke and 2-Stroke Engines\n\nBefore delving deeper into the 4-stroke bikes, it's essential to understand the fundamental differences between 4-stroke and 2-stroke engines, as this knowledge aids in appreciating the advantages of 4-stroke motorcycles.\n\n**A. Working Principle**\n\n- **2-Stroke Engines:** These complete a power cycle in two piston movements: compression and explosion.\n  \n- **4-Stroke Engines:** These require four piston movements: intake, compression, power, and exhaust.\n\n**B. Fuel Efficiency**\n\n- **2-Stroke:** Generally less fuel-efficient due to oil mixed with fuel and unburned fuel in the exhaust.\n  \n- **4-Stroke:** More fuel-efficient as they burn fuel only during the power strokes, with better lubrication systems.\n\n**C. Emissions**\n\n- **2-Stroke:** Higher emissions due to oil mixed with fuel and incomplete combustion.\n  \n- **4-Stroke:** Lower emissions, meeting stricter environmental regulations.\n\n**D. Maintenance**\n\n- **2-Stroke:** Fewer moving parts, simpler design, but may require more frequent oil changes.\n  \n- **4-Stroke:** More complex with more moving parts, but generally lower maintenance requirements over time.\n\n### Advantages of 4-Stroke Bikes\n\nChoosing a 4-stroke bike comes with several benefits that cater to both new and experienced riders:\n\n**1. Better Fuel Efficiency:**\n\nThe 4-stroke engine's design allows for more controlled fuel combustion, translating to better mileage, which is crucial for daily commuters.\n\n**2. Lower Emissions:**\n\nWith advancements in technology, 4-stroke engines comply with stringent emission norms, making them more environmentally friendly.\n\n**3. Enhanced Durability:**\n\nThe robust construction and efficient lubrication systems contribute to the longevity and reliability of 4-stroke bikes.\n\n**4. Power and Performance:**\n\nDespite having more components, 4-stroke engines deliver consistent and smooth power delivery, suitable for both city rides and highway cruising.\n\n### Factors to Consider When Choosing a 4-Stroke Bike\n\nWhen selecting the ideal 4-stroke motorcycle, several factors warrant consideration to ensure it aligns with your needs and preferences:\n\n**A. Purpose and Usage**\n\nIdentify whether the bike is primarily for commuting, sports riding, touring, or off-roading. Different bikes are optimized for various riding conditions.\n\n**B. Budget**\n\nEstablish a budget that includes not just the initial purchase cost but also ongoing expenses like insurance, maintenance, and fuel.\n\n**C. Engine Capacity**\n\nDetermine the engine size based on your riding experience and power requirements. Smaller engines are more fuel-efficient, while larger engines offer better performance.\n\n**D. Brand and After-Sales Service**\n\nResearch the brand's reputation, availability of spare parts, and quality of customer support. A reliable after-sales network ensures a smoother ownership experience.\n\n**E. Features and Comfort**\n\nLook for features like digital displays, ABS (Anti-lock Braking System), dual-channel setup, and ergonomic design that enhance safety and comfort during rides.\n\n**F. Resale Value**\n\nConsider models with higher resale value as they can offer better returns if you decide to upgrade in the future.\n\n### Detailed Analysis of Selected 4-Stroke Bikes\n\nLet's take a closer look at the aforementioned 4-stroke motorcycles, analyzing their strengths and potential limitations.\n\n**1. Bajaj Pulsar 150**\n\nThe Bajaj Pulsar 150 stands as a cornerstone in the Indian motorcycle market, known for its balance of performance and affordability.\n\n**Pros:**\n\n- **Performance:** Offers decent power output suitable for both city and highway riding.\n  \n- **Maintenance:** Bajaj's widespread service network ensures parts are readily available.\n  \n- **Design:** Stylish exterior with sporty graphics appeals to younger riders.\n\n**Cons:**\n\n- **Service Costs:** Being a popular model, service costs can sometimes be higher if not serviced through authorized centers.\n  \n- **Ride Comfort:** The seat might not be the most comfortable for long rides.\n\n**2. Bajaj Pulsar NS200**\n\nThe Pulsar NS200 targets enthusiasts who seek adrenaline-packed rides without the steep price tag of high-end sports bikes.\n\n**Pros:**\n\n- **Power Delivery:** The robust engine provides exhilarating performance.\n  \n- **Technology:** Features like the perimeter Frame enhance bike handling and stability.\n  \n- **Aesthetics:** Striking design elements make it a \u8857\u5934\u9738\u738b with a unique appearance.\n\n**Cons:**\n\n- **Fuel Consumption:** Higher engine capacity can lead to increased fuel consumption during aggressive riding.\n  \n- **City Commuting:** Its sporty nature might not be the best suited for stop-and-go traffic.\n\n**3. Hero Splendor Plus**\n\nThe Splendor Plus is a testament to Hero's dedication to producing reliable and efficient motorcycles.\n\n**Pros:**\n\n- **Fuel Efficiency:** Economical fuel consumption makes it ideal for daily commutes.\n  \n- **Reliability:** Known for minimal maintenance issues over extended periods.\n  \n- **Affordability:** One of the most budget-friendly options in the market.\n\n**Cons:**\n\n- **Performance:** Limited power output might feel underwhelming for riders seeking thrilling rides.\n  \n- **Styling:** Design remains traditional, which may not appeal to those preferring modern aesthetics.\n\n**4. TVS Apache RTR 160 4V**\n\nThe Apache RTR 160 4V from TVS motorcycles is a blend of performance and advanced features catering to urban riders.\n\n**Pros:**\n\n- **Features:** Triple racing mode, race tuned suspension, and a slipper clutch enhance the riding experience.\n  \n- **Handling:** Precise handling ensures confidence during swift city maneuvers.\n  \n- **Value for Money:** Packed with features at a competitive price point.\n\n**Cons:**\n\n- **Servicing:** While TVS has a decent service network, availability might vary in certain regions.\n  \n- **Comfort:** Aggressive ergonomics may not suit long-distance touring enthusiasts.\n\n**5. Royal Enfield Classic 350**\n\nThe Classic 350 embodies Royal Enfield's heritage, offering a retro experience with modern engineering.\n\n**Pros:**\n\n- **Styling:** Timeless design evoking a sense of nostalgia.\n  \n- **Ride Comfort:** Stable and smooth ride quality suitable for lengthy journeys.\n  \n- **Brand Loyalty:** Strong resale value and a dedicated owner's community.\n\n**Cons:**\n\n- **Performance:** While adequate, the engine might feel underpowered compared to higher-displacement bikes.\n  \n- **Maintenance:** Being a larger bike, maintenance costs can be  marginally higher.\n\n### Emerging Trends in 4-Stroke Motorcycles\n\nAs technology advances, the Indian motorcycle market witnesses several trends shaping the future of 4-stroke bikes:\n\n**A. Fuel Injection Systems**\n\nModern bikes are increasingly adopting fuel injection over carburetors, offering better fuel efficiency, smoother throttle response, and reduced emissions.\n\n**B. Anti-lock Braking Systems (ABS)**\n\nSafety features like ABS are becoming standard or optional across many models, enhancing braking performance and rider safety.\n\n**C. Hybrid and Electric Variants**\n\nWhile still in developmental stages, hybrid and fully electric bikes are gaining traction, promising reduced carbon footprints and enhanced sustainability.\n\n**D. Advanced Display and Connectivity**\n\nDigital instrument clusters with smartphone connectivity for navigation and ride analytics are becoming more prevalent, enriching the riding experience.\n\n### Conclusion\n\n4-stroke motorcycles dominate the Indian two-wheeler market, offering a perfect blend of power, efficiency, and reliability. Whether you're a beginner looking for a dependable commuter like the Hero Splendor Plus or an enthusiast craving the performance of the Bajaj Pulsar NS200, there's a 4-stroke bike tailored to your needs. When making a choice, consider factors like purpose, budget, and desired features to ensure you select a motorcycle that aligns with your lifestyle and riding preferences.\n\n---",
